  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>You weave a collection of handseals conjuring a large incomprehensible monstrosity known as Mh'ithrha that hovers above you. Select a number of creatures that you can see and that can see you within range, equal to your proficiency bonus. Each selected creature can see this  onstrosity as its visage and design goes against all things rational and sane. The selected creature must succeed an Intelligence saving throw.</p><p>Critical Success: Affected creature is able to resist this Jutsu's effects becoming immune to it for the next minute cast from the same creature.</p><p>Success: Affected creature is able to resist this jutsu's effects.</p><p>Failure: Affected creature takes 4d6 psychic damage and gains 1 rank of Concussion.</p><p>Critical Failure: Affected creature takes 4d6 + Genjutsu ability modifier psychic damage and gains 2 ranks of Concussion.</p>",
